  "text": "Multiple alignment of the MhyF and the large subunits of various [NiFe] hydrogenases from the group of H 2 -evolving, energy-conserving, membrane-associated hydrogenases revealed an N-terminal extension, which was present only in the MhyF subunit and in the hydrogenase large subunits of the formate hydrogenlyase systems (E. coli HycE [CITATION_1] , HyfG [CITATION_2] ). This stretch was proposed to play a role in the interaction between the two enzymes the hydrogenase and the formate dehydrogenase [CITATION_3] .",
